<!--

nan chun by pouthongwon

a dual sidebar theme with a tabbed modal and (optional) custom links on click

note #1: don't alter, move, or delete my credit in the bottom right corner or in this code

note #2: everything can be edited in the 'customize' panel, so don't worry about getting into the code â€”except when you want to add something

note #3: if you want to replace the sideblog images, follow these steps:

step 1) find the image you want to use (or, if you want to use your tumblr avatar, this is the format: //api.tumblr.com/v2/blog/[Sideblog Name].tumblr.com/avatar)
step 2) right click on the image, there'll be a few options when you do that
step 3) find 'copy image url' (or something similar) and click on it, the url is now copied to your clipboard
step 4) go to the customize panel and find 'Sideblog [#] Image', there will be a string of text underneath it
step 5) delete the text and paste the image url you've copied

credits:
fonts by google fonts
icons by solar icons
base code by @mournstera (+ light/dark toggle, poll post styling, and the following scripts: unifyaudio, shorten notecount, and timeago)
- modal by geeksforgeeks
- accessible tabs by code concisely
- modified scroll to top tutorial by w3schools
- images are from a variety of places (notably, various korean actors'/models' instagrams for the sideblogs and sidebar. pexels for the modal images)
- theme title from 'nan chun' by se so neon and custom title + description are from the same song, translated by ana on youtube
    - link: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TmgU7GVj7yo

-->



